<para id="RM000000ZQ200ZX" category="D" type-id="303I1" name-id="ES0OA-30" from="201202">
<name>CHECK FOR INTERMITTENT PROBLEMS</name>
<subpara id="RM000000ZQ200ZX_z0" proc-id="RM21Q0EV__00000FL00000">
<content5 releasenbr="4">
<atten4>
<ptxt>Intelligent tester:</ptxt>
<ptxt>Inspect the vehicle's ECM using check mode. Intermittent problems are easier to detect with an intelligent tester when the ECM is in check mode. In check mode, the ECM uses 1 trip detection logic, which has a higher sensitivity to malfunctions than normal mode (default), which uses 2 trip detection logic.</ptxt>
</atten4>
<list1 type="ordered">
<item>
<ptxt>Clear the DTCs (see page <xref label="Seep01" href="RM000000ZPW01AX"/>).</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>Change the ECM from normal mode to check mode using the intelligent tester (see page <xref label="Seep02" href="RM000000ZPX00PX"/>).</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>Perform a simulation test.</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>Check the connectors and terminals.</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>Wiggle the harnesses and connectors.</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</content5>
</subpara>
</para>
